The paper deals with the design of control policies for robots, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on safety constraints and forbidden regions suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of a convex program inspired by entropy maximization principles suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
